<article>
    <h1>IN&#xAD;GRE&#xAD;DI&#xAD;ENTS</h1>
    <h2>Won&#xAD;der&#xAD;ing what to cook to&#xAD;day? In this daily se&#xAD;ries, STFood On&#xAD;line Ed&#xAD;i&#xAD;tor Hedy Khoo whips up easy eats to try at home</h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20200716/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-07-16"><time>2020-07-16</time></a>
        - <span>LIFE</span>
        - <span role="byline">5 crab shells 454g pas&#xAD;teurised crab claw meat 20g panko (Ja&#xAD;panese bread&#xAD;crumbs) 20g Chi&#xAD;nese cel&#xAD;ery, chopped 15g spring onion, sliced&#xD;&#xA;1 red fin&#xAD;ger chilli (15g), coarsely chopped&#xD;&#xA;1 green fin&#xAD;ger chilli (15g), coarsely chopped&#xD;&#xA;1 red onion (110g), chopped 3 </span>
    </section>

    <p>METHOD</p>
    <p>1. Put crab meat in a bowl. Add panko, cel­ery, spring onion, sliced chill­ies, red onion and gar­lic. Mix well. 3. Fill each crab shell with about 140g of crab mix­ture. Place shells on a plate and wrap with cling film. Leave them in the fridge for two hours to help the mix­ture firm up.</p>
    <p>4. Heat 400ml of oil in a wok. Place three crab shells, fill­ing side down, in the oil. Lower the heat to medium-low. Fry for three min­utes un­til the fill­ing is golden-brown. Turn the shells over and fry for another two min­utes.</p>

